.TH MPI_Bsend 3 "12/15/1994" " " "MPI"
.SH NAME
MPI_Bsend \- Basic send with user-specified buffering

.SH INPUT PARAMETERS
.PD 0
.TP
.B buf 
- initial address of send buffer (choice) 
.PD 1
.PD 0
.TP
.B count 
- number of elements in send buffer (nonnegative integer) 
.PD 1
.PD 0
.TP
.B datatype 
- datatype of each send buffer element (handle) 
.PD 1
.PD 0
.TP
.B dest 
- rank of destination (integer) 
.PD 1
.PD 0
.TP
.B tag 
- message tag (integer) 
.PD 1
.PD 0
.TP
.B comm 
- communicator (handle) 
.PD 1

.SH NOTES
This send is provided as a convenience function; it allows the user to
send messages without worring about where they are buffered (because the
user MUST have provided buffer space with MPI_Buffer_attach).
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
#include "mpi.h"
int MPI_Bsend( buf, count, datatype, dest, tag, comm )
void             *buf;
int              count, dest, tag;
MPI_Datatype     datatype;
MPI_Comm         comm;

.fi

.SH LOCATION
 bsend.c
